            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Hd1e108">Rubrica 18</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De iuramenti religione</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#P"/>De iuramenti religione. ca: xviii -
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Rd1e116">In leuitico. capitulo. xviiii.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Qd1e125" source="http://scta.info/resource/lev19_12@1-10">Non iurabis in nomine
               <lb ed="#P"/>meo nec pollues nomen domini dei.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e133">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Rd1e132">Yesus Filius sirach in ecclesiastico. capitulo. xxiii.</ref>
               <lb ed="#P"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Qd1e137" source="http://scta.info/resource/sir23_9@1-10 http://scta.info/resource/sir23_12@1-5">Iurationi non assuescat os tuum. Multi enim
               <lb ed="#P"/>casus in illa. Vir multum iurans replebitur in
               <lb ed="#P" break="no"/>iquitate.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e148">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Rd1e149">Mattheus in euangelo. ca. v.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Qd1e152" source="http://scta.info/resource/mt5_34@5-14  http://scta.info/resource/mt5_35@1-16  http://scta.info/resource/mt5_36@1-14  http://scta.info/resource/mt5_37@1-16">noli iurare omnio neque
               <lb ed="#P"/>per celum quia tronus dei est. neque perterram
               <lb ed="#P"/>quia scabellum pedis eius est: neque per <sic>Ie
               <lb ed="#P" break="no"/>rosolimam</sic> <!--hierosolymam--> quia ciuitas est magni regis
               <cb ed="#P" n="b"/>
               <lb ed="#P"/>neque percaput tuum inurabis quia non potes
               <lb ed="#P"/>vnum capillum facere album vel nigrum
               <lb ed="#P"/>Si autem sermo vester et est. non. non. quod autem
               <lb ed="#P"/>ampluis est a malo est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e171">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Rd1e174">Iacobus epistola. primo. ca. v. et fi:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Qd1e175" source="http://scta.info/resource/iac5_12@6-24">Nolite iura
               <lb ed="#P" break="no"/>re neque per celum neque per terram neque per
               <lb ed="#P"/>aliud inuramentum si autem sermo vester est
               <lb ed="#P"/>non, non,.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e185">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Rd1e190">Paulus ad ebreos. capitulo. vi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Qd1e189" source="http://scta.info/resource/hebr6_16@1-15">homines per ma
               <lb ed="#P" break="no"/>iorem sui iurant et omnis controuersie eorum
               <lb ed="#P"/>finis ad confirmationem est iuramentum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e199">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Rd1e206">Cato. ca. primo. iusiurandum serua.</ref>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e207">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Rd1e215">Isidorus in sinonomia solilorum libro
               <lb ed="#P"/>. ii. ca. xxv.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Qd1e211">assiduitas per iurii consue
               <lb ed="#P" break="no"/>tudinem facit usus iuris suirandi ad per
               <lb ed="#P" break="no"/>iurium ducit sic in ore tuo est sic sic
               <lb ed="#P"/>in ore tuo non est: veritas iuramento non
               <lb ed="#P"/>indiget</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-d1e223"> <!--Combined with above-->
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de4661-Qd1e225">forma sit sacramenti tui fidess</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
